Part of the constellation was hived off to form the constellation Sciurus Volans, the Flying Squirrel, by William Croswell in [[1810]]. However this was not taken up by later cartographers.<ref>{{cite book | first=Nick | last=Kanas | date=2007 | title=Star maps: history, artistry, and cartography | page=131 |url=https://books.google.com.au/books?id=bae3LP4tfP4C&pg=PA131 | publisher=Springer |location=New York, New York | isbn=0-387-71668-8 }}</ref>
