==Visualizations==

[[H. A. Rey]] has suggested an alternative way to connect the stars of Camelopardalis into a giraffe figure.
[[File:Camelopardalis constellation map visualization.PNG|thumb|Diagram of H. A. Rey's method of connecting the stars of the constellation Camelopardalis, in order to show a giraffe.]]
{{clear|left}}

The giraffe's body consists of the quadrangle of stars α Cam, β Cam, [[BE Camelopardalis|BE Cam]], and [[Gamma Camelopardalis|γ Cam]]: α Cam and β Cam being of the fourth magnitude. The stars [[HD 42818]] (HR 2209) and [[M Camelopardalis|M Cam]] form the [[head]] of the giraffe, and the stars M Cam and α Cam form the giraffe's long [[neck]]. Stars β Cam and [[7 Camelopardalis|7 Cam]] form the giraffe's front leg, and [[variable star]]s BE Cam and CS Cam form the giraffe's hind leg.

==Equivalents==
In [[Chinese astronomy]], the stars of Camelopardalis are located within a group of circumpolar stars called the [[Purple Forbidden Enclosure]] (紫微垣 ''Zǐ Wēi Yuán'').

